<doc id="640266" wikidata="Q523000" url="?curid=640266" title="Kitale">
<text>Kitale is a town in the north west of Kenya, in the former Rift Valley province, between Mount Elgon and the Cherangany Hills. It has an elevation of around . Its population was as of 2019. It is the location of Kitale Airport.

The National Museum of Western Kenya in Kitale is a natural history museum.

==Location==
Kitale lies between Mount Elgon and Cherang&#x27;any Hills is 72.3 km (44.9 mi) by road north west of Eldoret.

==History==
In 1920 Arthur Champion, the colonial district commissioner, established a new headquarters in the Trans Nzoia at the future sure of the township of Kitale.

In 1930 locusts caused extensive damage to crops.

== Climate ==
Kitale has a temperate oceanic climate (Köppen climate classification &quot;Cfb&quot;).


